<font color="#FF0000">LYNDA VAN DEVANTER</font><br>
<tt>Sat May 17  3:45:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
&quot;Home Before Morning,&quot; by Lynda Van Devanter is one hell<br>
of a moving book!  Everyone from my generation and the <br>
ones to follow should read it.  &quot;Visions of War, Dreams of <br>
Peace,&quot; is next on my list to read.  May all the Lynda's out<br>
there speak up loud and clear.  Let us know your pain and<br>
your love.  We are standing beside you and will never forget<br>
you. <br><br>
I was born in 1966.  It took many years of personal growth to <br>
understand all that was going on while I was growing up.  I<br>
know that I will never forget anyone who was involved with<br>
the Vietnam War.  All of you will be remembered with me...<br><br>

